snippet.textDisplay:
The story that I thought I would never tell to anyone except her, but now I think it’s time to share, begins when I was in 6th grade. There was a girl that all the boys in my class liked. I was a shy child, so whenever I tried to talk to any girl, I became shy and nervous. One boy proposed to her, and she said no. Another boy was trying to propose to her, and at that time, I fell in love with her. I wanted that boy to get rejected. In the flow of first love, I shared my feelings with a friend, and he told the boy about it. Then, the boy and his friends came to beat me, but that time, she protected me. I was so scared, but that day, I saw love in her eyes. After that, the boy was rejected, and I was happy. We used to talk a lot in class, and I only went to school for her. Everything was going perfect; her friends would tease me, but she would protect me.

Then one day, I made the biggest mistake of my life. I was going to my friend's house with my friend, and she and her friends were behind us. Suddenly, her friend teased me, and I got a little nervous. She said, "Don’t get nervous, her friend only wants to irritate you." When we reached my friend's house, she called me over. I got so nervous that I ignored her. She had a letter with her, and I regret that now. Later, on the second-last day of our exams, my friends and she were playing truth or dare. My friend asked her if she liked me, and she said, “I am not equal to her shoe.” On the last day, she came to me, trying to get me to agree, but I got nervous and ignored her again. She told my friend that she would not talk to me because I didn’t even look at her. After that, she and her friend fought for a reason that i don't know, me and she stopped talking because her friend was talking to me. However, after a month, we started talking again.

On Valentine's Day, my friend and I were playing something on the blackboard when she came into the class. I got nervous and went outside. She came to me and said, "Come, let’s play together." She held my hand, and we went back inside. But we didn’t play because my friends were still playing on the blackboard. While waiting for my friends to finish, she held my hand for 5 minutes. Her friend teased her, and she smiled. But as usual, I got nervous and went to the washroom. When I came back, the teacher was there. That day, I also forgot to bring a pen, so I asked my friend, and he said I should ask her. She gave me her pen. Nowadays, I see her looking at me, and I am happy to have another chance. But not everyone gets a second chance So Don't Get Dumb like me . I like this song because it makes me fall in love more with her every time I listen to it.

❣❣



Edit: I blocked her because she became best friends with the boy who was coming to beat me.
